rComments: Probably the worst prof I know. Very condescending. Rude and very unapproachable. Lectures are boring, she's all over the place and she uses horrible memes to try to be funny.

Sytsma is a very divisive professor in the Criminology department some people love her and some really have some mean things to say. For me she has always been fun and engaging. My biggest critique is that exams can be difficult in the sense that some of the questions she asks are from minor points in a single slide
Cocky, rude. Tries to be funny and hears crickets. My least favourite prof in 4 years.

Sytsma is super funny and tries to make class light and fun.  She posts slides in advance and allows you to fill parts in during lecture.  She connects material to current day events and shows lots of videos! Great class to take.
The worst professor I've ever had. Very condescending and boring. Will not be taking her again.

Her lectures are basically condensations of the textbook, but it doesn't matter in the long run because she's very clear and tries to make the dry material bearable with media clips and her cute humour. Her Jeopardy reviews were also fun. Assignments are repetitive, however, and the final test was disproportionately more difficult than the first.

She reads off of slides which are directly copied and pasted from the course textbook. She tries to be funny but fails miserably. She's arrogant, rude & full of herself. Overall, a bad professor and I wouldn't recommend taking classes with her.
